                                        <comments>
                            <comment id="31427" author="robert.kasanicky" created="Tue, 29 Jan 2008 22:05:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;As far as I am aware this attribute is meant for optimistic locking support - so it has technical nature (rather than domain meaning).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="31439" author="david_syer" created="Wed, 30 Jan 2008 01:26:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes, it&apos;s for optimistic locking.  It&apos;s even used in the StepExecution.  But not the other entities I think.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="31450" author="douglas.c.kaminsky" created="Wed, 30 Jan 2008 05:12:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;That&apos;s not entirely clear from the name, in any case. As of m3, when I search the code, there isn&apos;t a single call to entity.getVersion() outside of tests and no mention of the VERSION field at all in the DAO classes except where it is set to zero for step executions.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Can you elaborate on what the indended purpose of this was? It seems like an incomplete thought at present.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="32905" author="david_syer" created="Wed, 5 Mar 2008 23:23:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The Map dao should respect the same version update semantics as the SQL one if possible.  And the JobExecution and JobInstance should have their versions updated by the daos as well.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="32913" author="robert.kasanicky" created="Thu, 6 Mar 2008 00:50:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think version should be removed from JobInstance, given the semantics JobInstance = Job + JobParameters. JobInstance is fundamentally static data - just created, not updated.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For JobExecution I&apos;m not sure whether we need the version - I suppose it is not expected to be updated concurrenlty.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="32919" author="david_syer" created="Thu, 6 Mar 2008 01:41:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We might as well just use version for a static JobInstance then.  Probably nothing to do there.  The JobExecution should not be updated concurrently, so nothing fancy needed I think.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="33018" author="robert.kasanicky" created="Sat, 8 Mar 2008 06:59:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;All daos now increment the version on save/update - only StepExecutionDaos test the value for concurrent modifications though&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="38445" author="david_syer" created="Thu, 7 Aug 2008 02:06:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Assume closed as resolved and released&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
